30/04/2003
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska (RS) Prime Minister Dragan Mikerevic said Tuesday (29 April) that he is waiting for the Office of the High Representative to approve his nominee for finance minister, Branko Krsmanovic.
Mikerevic says he submitted the name late last week.
Krsmanovic, 43, is an assistant professor at the Banja Luka School of Economics and advises Mikerevic on transition issues.
Former RS Finance Minister Simeun Vilendecic resigned in late February after a banking scandal in the entity.
(OHR Sources - 30/04/03;
Onasa - 29/04/03)
